This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image and image set classification. The use of discriminative graph constraints also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of non-negative projection and dictionary learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of image sets suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
